parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure Leading to Vehicle Fires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause vehicle fires, which can result in serious injury or death, as well as significant property damage.
symptoms: White smoke coming from the front end of the car
arcing and shorting out of electrical circuits.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Body Sticking and Unwanted Sudden Acceleration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking of the throttle body can cause unwanted sudden acceleration, which can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: the vehicle accelerates without driver input
the brake pedal becomes inoperative or is unable to stop the vehicle
the only way to stop the vehicle is to turn off the ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the cruise control vacuum line can cause unwanted sudden acceleration, which can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The cruise control vacuum line kinks or becomes restricted
the brake pedal becomes inoperative or is unable to stop the vehicle
the only way to stop the vehicle is to turn off the ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire Tread Separation and Sidewall Cracking
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation and sidewall cracking can lead to sudden tire failure, loss of vehicle control, and accidents, posing a significant risk to driver and passenger safety.
Wheel separation can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, posing a significant risk to driver and passenger safety.
Worn steering bushings can cause loose steering, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle stability.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or wobbly
the vehicle wanders or drifts while driving
the steering wheel requires more effort to turn
unusual noises or clunking sounds while steering.
